  • Classes in com.spazedog.lib.rootfw4 used by com.spazedog.lib.rootfw4 
    Class and Description
    RootFW.OnConnectionListener
    An interface that can be used to monitor the current state of the global connection.
    Shell.Attempts
    A class containing automatically created shell attempts and links to both Shell#executeAsync(String[], Integer[], OnShellResultListener) and Shell#execute(String[], Integer[])

    All attempts are created based on Common.BINARIES.
    Shell.OnShellBroadcastListener
    This interface is used internally across utility classes.
    Shell.OnShellConnectionListener
    This interface is used to get information about connection changes.
    Shell.OnShellResultListener
    This interface is for use with Shell.executeAsync(String[], OnShellResultListener).
    Shell.OnShellValidateListener
    This interface is for use with the execute methods.
    Shell.Result
    This class is used to store the result from shell executions.
    Shell.StreamCollector
    This is mostly an internal class that is used to collect data from the ShellStreamer.
    ShellStream.OnStreamListener
    Deprecated. 
    This has been deprecated along with it's parent ShellStream. It has been replaced by ShellStreamer.StreamListener and ShellStreamer.ConnectionListener to be used with the new ShellStreamer class.
    ShellStreamer
    This class replaces the old ShellStream.

    This works as an extended version of Java's Process class.
    ShellStreamer.ConnectionListener
    Listener interface that will provide notice about this streams connection state.
    ShellStreamer.StreamListener
    Listener interface that will provide details and data from streams

    This interface can be added both locally or globally.
